<br>
I came into some money and decided, ok ill buy it.  First mistake was for the price i paid i was getting too much and was too blinded by the luck i had fallen into to realize that this was going to eventually go bad.  Hayley informed me that he was going to move 2 low levle chars off the account and that i shouldnt change the password or billing info for the time being, this was confirmed by *the original Garoth* who owned Garoth (the character).  <br>
<br>
To be honest, if my memory serves me correct this was actually all brought on by me wanting to get my epics and Hayley telling me to buy all the MQ's because FS couldnt raid PoA.  So i bought the account, leveled it up to 65, pumped out some AA's, got him epics and then realized that i made a huge mistake buying a account that with a weeks worth of work outgrew FS's capabilities.  <br>
<br>
Anyways back to the issue at hand, almost the whole summer went by without a word from *the original Garoth*.  At the end of the summer *the original Garoth* e-mailed me and said he would like 13 dollars for the month he had to pay for because i didnt cancel the billing.  Now to no big surprise im 17 and dont have a credit card that i can just use at random to paypal someone 13 dollars.  So i told him ill cancel the billing and when i can ill send him 13 dollars, also included the fact i never recieved an e-mail prior to that saying he wasnt going to move his 2 characters.  <br>
<br>
I informed Hayley that *the original Garoth* sent me an e-mail and she said it was his fault for not canceling it, and made a joke about the whole thing, it was her who said that he never checks his CC bill and that i could probaly keep using his billing info for awhile.  I had already canceled the billing before logging into the game so that wasnt even an option at this point.  A week later completely having a blonde moment i ordered LDoN thinking i was on Cenodars account.<br>
<br>
At the time i was trying to sell Cenodar's account because i had no use for 2 warrior accounts, so having the expansion on that account could help bring up its worthless value.  Anyways after buying the expansion and not even realizing it was put onto *the original Garoth's* CC, you would think there are safeguards that would stop you or atleast ask you if you want to bill something onto a canceled credit card.  Anyways, that day i decided i was going to take a break from EQ and quit FS because i didnt want to have any loose ends just incase i decide to sell the account.  The day after i had 10 failed attempts at logging in when i logged in, i asked Hayley if she tried to access the account for whatever her reasons were, seeing as she was completely irrational about me leaving FS.  She said *the original Garoth* was trying to access to account to end the billing and refused to give me his cell phone number to call him and talk to him.  <br>
<br>
That could have avoided this whole thing.  The next day the password was invalid and i recieve an e-mail from him saying i was just renting his account and then yelled at me for missing items.  Surprise that when i logged onto the game that day on Cenodar i find Garoth retagged for FS, hmm i wonder if maybe *Hayley* had something to do with this whole thing.  She had my cell phone number she could have given that to *the original Garoth* so he could have talked to me before taking the account back but in all fairness without any other options i too would have changed the password and canceled the billing and then given back the account, or if my CC was being billed, i would have called EQ or my CC provider and told them to stop billing.  <br>
<br>
